<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meri Comments on State Visits to Israel, Ukraine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703210994 Tallinn ETA in English 1753 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1703210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 17 -- President Lennart Meri arrived 
from a visit to Ukraine on Thursday [17 March] and gave a news 
conference at the Tallinn airport. 
  On commenting his earlier visit to Israel, Meri recalled as 
most remarkable language-teaching to immigrants. It was 
interesting to see how in only six months a person virtually 
melts into the society, Meri said. Meri also said that after 
meetings with the president, prime minister, foreign minister 
and representatives of the Israeli parliament, he knows that 
Israel understands the tasks that lie ahead of Estonia. 
  On commenting on Ukraine, Meri said he thought the west 
often 
made a mistake in talking of the Baltic countries and former 
regions of the defunct Soviet Union. Ukraine is one of the 
biggest European countries, Meri said. We could see ourselves 
that gigantic economic reforms lie ahead of Ukraine and that the 
country intends to build a strong independent state which would 
be open to all countries of the world, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

