<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Amends Law on Privatized Housing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703155994 Tallinn BNS in English 1057 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1703155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 17, BNS -- The Estonian parliament on 
Wednesday [16 March] passed amendments to the law on the 
privatization of housing. 
  The amendments say the privatization voucher issued to 
Estonia's residents for their years of work may be transferred 
as a gift to the holder's parents, spouse, relatives in the 
descending line, sisters, brothers and their relatives, who are 
Estonian citizens or permanent residents of the country. 
  The law also gives the municipal and local commune 
governments the right to determine the houses that cannot be 
privatized because of plans to pull them down, their 
reconstruction, further use, or some other reason. The reason 
for the refusal must be made public. 
  Non-occupied housing premises can be privatized by Estonian 
residents of at least 18 years of age. The law says years of 
service in the KGB shall not be accounted in calculation of the 
length of employment in Estonia. 
  The parliament also approved an amendment to the tax 
regulations law, giving the government the right to extinguish 
debts of state companies going to privatization, or participate 
in management of the debts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

