<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Damage Pay Ordered for Naming Alleged Informers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703210894 Tallinn ETA in English 1753 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1703210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 17 -- An Estonian weekly must pay 
damages and apologize publicly for publishing a list of alleged 
KGB informers in five articles last spring, the Tallinn City 
Court ruled on Thursday [17 March]. 
  The court ruled the published data was false and the owner 
of 
the paper, AS Myyt, must in ten days apologize in the weekly 
"Eesti Aeg"( Estonian time) before the seven plaintiffs and play 
damages in the amount of 70,000 kroons ($5,000). 
  "Eesti Aeg" in its five issues last spring published the 
list 
of alleged KGB informers claiming the list had been found in a 
notebook of a KGB officer. 
  The list was quite lengthy, but only seven people decided to 
take legal action. 

</TEXT>

