<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   British Government `Speaks Highly' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703182994 Tallinn BNS in English 1619 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1703182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 17, BNS -- The British Government issued 
a press statement Wednesday [16 March] in which it speaks highly 
of the Latvian-Russian interstate agreements, which were 
initialed March 14 in Moscow. 
  Under the agreements, Russia makes a commitment to get its 
remaining 12,000 troops out of Latvia by Aug. 31 while Latvia 
agrees that Russia operates the former Soviet military radar at 
Skrunda for four years and have 18 months to dismantle it. 
  The British Government hopes that similar agreements will 
soon be concluded between Estonia and Russia, according to the 
statement. 

</TEXT>

