<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protest Seeks Immediate Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703175194 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 17 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A gathering of about 300 people protesting against 
the initialling of the Russian-Latvian interstate agreement and 
the functioning of the Skrunda radar station in Latvia after 31 
August 1994 was held today at the Saeima building before the 
opening of a plenary session. The pickets demanded the 
immediate withdrawal of the occupying Russian army from the 
territory of Latvia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16613 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov053_u_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-053 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ostankino Given Demand To Pay Debt `Immediately' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803033494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 2335 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803033494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Latvia demands that the Ostankino television company 
immediately pay its debt for the transmission of its TV programs 
in the republic. 
  At a meeting in Riga Thursday the Latvian Council for TV and 
Radio Broadcasting decided to notify Ostankino that if by April 
4 the debt for the 1st quarter is not repaid to Latvia, it will 
immediately consider cutting off the transmission of Ostankino 
TV programs on its territory. 
  So far, Ostankino has paid to the Latvian Council for TV and 
Radio Broadcasting only one third of the agreed amount. 
  Chairman of the Council Zigmunds Skujins said at the meeting 
that it is impossible to meet the demand of the second major 
faction of the Latvian parliament, the Movement for National 
Independence of Latvia, that the transmission of some Ostankino 
programs be stopped for political reasons. 

</TEXT>

