<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former KGB Chief Arrested on `Genocide Charges' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1703183694 Tallinn BNS in English 1619 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1703183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 17, BNS -- The former Soviet Latvia's KGB 
chief, Alfons Noviks, was arrested Tuesday [15 March] on 
genocide charges. 
  During his active service in 1940s, Noviks conducted mass 
murders, persecutions and deportation of those Latvian residents 
who were unwelcome to the Soviet regime. 
  If convicted, Noviks faces three to 15 years in prison or 
life imprisonment. 
  Noviks was born in 1908. 

</TEXT>

