<H3> <TI>   Attends Conversion Committee Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703195694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] At today's sitting of the Russian-American committee 
on conversion, Andrey Kokoshin, the Russian first deputy defense 
minister, and U.S. Defense Secretary William Perry stressed that 
Russia and America are entering a new phase of their 
relationship. Their speeches noted that the talk should now be 
not only about future prospects but also about specific ways to 
implement the conversion of Russia's defense complex. 
  The American side showed an interest in assisting Russia's 
conversion plans, not just with advice but also with hundreds of 
millions of dollars. In particular, William Perry emphasized 
the wish of the Americans to organize in Russia the manufacture 
of prefabricated housing for servicemen's families, and noted 
the mutual benefit of cooperation between the two countries on 
this issue. 

