<H3> <TI>   Czech Delegation Ends Visit; Friendship Treaty Discussed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803095694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0836 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vladimir Taranov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 1 TASS [dateline as received] -- 
"There are good grounds for the ratification of treaty of the 
friendly relations between Russia and Czechia," Jiri Pein, the 
chairman of the foreign relations committee of the chamber of 
deputies of the Czech Republic, told ITAR-TASS upon the 
conclusion of a visit of a parliamentary delegation of the Czech 
Republic to Moscow. He said the Russian side promised to speed 
up the ratification of the treaty which is of much importance 
for creating the legal grounds for cooperation between Russia 
and Czechia. 
  The Czech parliamentarian said that meetings with leaders of 
the Russian State Duma and Federation Council, with 
representatives of the Russian Foreign Ministry and of Russian 
political parties indicated that changes had taken place in the 
Russian foreign policy. During meetings and conversations that 
the Czech parliamentary delegation had in Moscow the sides were 
not striving to convince each other of anything. They only 
exchanged opinions on matters of mutual interest, specifically, 
the attitude to the "Partnership for Peace", European security 
and prospects for economic cooperation. "We got convinced that 
Russia respects Czechia's sovereignty", Jiri Pein said. 

</TEXT>

