<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev Arrives in Kaliningrad; To Set Up Defense Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703162394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1549 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Biryukov] </F>
  [Text] Kaliningrad, 17 Mar -- "I am in Kaliningrad Oblast 
to resolve the issue of setting up a limited operational group 
made up from the forces of the Baltic Fleet and from the 
land-based forces." This was stated today by Russian Defense 
Minister Pavel Grachev on arrival in Kaliningrad. He has begun 
a three-day tour of inspection of the country's westernmost 
oblast. 
  According to the minister, the numerical strength of the 
group that is being set up "will be determined by the defensive 
sufficiency necessary to protect this enclave territory and also 
Russia's interests in the Baltic region." "The final decision 
on setting up the group and its deployment will be made by a 
Defense Ministry collegium," Pavel Grachev stressed. 

</TEXT>

