<F P=102>  LD1803084894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0830 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS Parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 18 TASS -- The Russian State Duma 
refused on Friday to discuss the cancellation of the agreement 
instituting the Commonwealth of Independent States which was 
signed by the leaders of Russia, Ukraine and Belarus in 1991 and 
which actually signalled the collapse of the former Soviet Union. 
  The proposal was submitted by Anatoliy Lukyanov, former 
speaker of the Soviet parliament, who faced trial as an 
organiser of the 1991 coup which resulted in the Soviet 
collapse, but was amnestied by the Duma. 
  Lukyanov is now a member of the "Russian Way" group in the 
Duma. 

