<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council To Ratify 100 Treaties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703155794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1306 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 17 TASS -- The Federation Council is to 
ratify some 100 international treaties, Russian Deputy Foreign 
Minister Boris Pastukhov said at a session of the upper chamber 
of the Russian parliament. About 40 of them are of a priority 
importance. The legislators will adopt a ratification law on 
each treaty. 
  Speaking about the ratification of the treaty between Russia 
and Georgia on friendship, cooperation and good neighbourly 
relations, Pastukhov called attention to article 33, which says 
that "the treaty shall be subject to ratification and shall 
become effective after the exchange of ratification instruments 
of the two countries." He pointed out that President Yeltsin had 
stressed before signing the treaty that "its ratification is 
possible only after obvious headway is made in the settlement of 
the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict." 
  According to Pastukhov, now the Russian Foreign Ministry and 
Defence Ministry are unanimous in their opinion that "not a 
single cartridge should be turned over to the Georgian side, not 
even for the needs of the Georgian Interior Ministry." He 
stressed the need for a closer cooperation between members of 
the Federation Council and the Foreign Ministry. 
  The Federation Council adopted today draft regulations on 
the 
parliamentary group of the Federal Assembly. According to 
Speaker of the Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko, the 
parliamentary group of the Federal Assembly will be made up of 
members of the State Duma and the Federation Council in order to 
represent the Russian parliament in international organisations. 
Aside from it, the Federation Council adopted a resolution on 
the creation of a hospitality fund. 
  The legislators adopted a resolution on the amount of 
monthly 
remuneration for members of the Federation Council holding 
elective posts. According to the resolution, 299,000 roubles 
will be added to their monthly salaries, equal to those of 
ministers, and to other privileges. According to Shumeyko, "the 
rise in wages is intended for members of Federation Council 
committees working on a full-time basis, as well as for deputies 
to the Federation Council to cover travelling expenses." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

