<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ostankino TV To Be Curtailed if Debt Not Repaid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703113394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0530 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The management of Lithuanian Radio and TV has 
officially announced the partial curtailment of the relay of the 
Ostankino TV channel if Ostankino does not pay its debt to 
Lithuanian communications men by the beginning of April. The 
decision has been taken, ANI agency notes, despite the fact that 
the Ostankino TV channel is the only Russian TV channel relayed 
throughout Lithuania and has the highest rating in the republic. 
According to the calculations of Lithuanian communications men, 
the debt of the transmitting station in Moscow equals 
approximately 1 billion lits or $250,000. Evidently it is 
appropriate to remember that in all civilized countries of the 
world it is the receiving side that pays for the transmission of 
broadcasts but in our country it is the other way round. 

</TEXT>

