<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to UN: Security Council Should Be Expanded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803111894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0900 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1803111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting of the UN General Assembly working 
group, Ukrainian Envoy to UN Oleksandr Mosych addressed the 
issue of just representation in the UN Security Council, and 
expanding its membership. He emphasized that the current 
composition of the UN Security Council, as well as its operation 
under the current multitude of work, requires that its number be 
increased, and that new regional circumstances and new 
participants in international relations be considered. 
  The implementation of this proposal would significantly 
improve the productivity level of the council that is a body 
acting in the name of all UN members, according to its statute 
responsibilities. At the same time, it is necessary to preserve 
all [words indistinct], to ensure that it immediately reacts to 
situations that require intervention, examining them, and 
adopting appropriate decisions. It is important to find 
compromises to resolve questions of membership in the Security 
Council, which would be acceptable to all countries, including 
the council's permanent members. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

