<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Space Forces Launch Cosmos-2274 From Plesetsk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703184094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1829 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS string correspondent Semen Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 17 TASS -- The Russian military space 
forces launched "Cosmos-2274" satellite with "Soyuz-5" carrier 
rocket from the Russian cosmodrome in Plesetsk at 19:30 Moscow 
time on Thursday. 
  According to the press centre of the military space forces, 
the launch was successful. 
  The space apparatus is moving at an orbit close to the 
estimated [sentence as received]. Its movements are monitored 
by the main centre for testing and controlling space apparatuses 
based in Golitsyno-2, a town in the Moscow region. The centre 
is a structural unit of the Russian military space forces. 
  "Cosmos-2274" was the 1086th satellite to be launched from 
the Plesetsk cosmodrome inaugurated 28 years ago. 

</TEXT>

