<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prospects for New Station Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803034194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0200 GMT 
18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803034194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Work to create a new Russian space launching ground 
is beginning at Svobodnyy in Amur Oblast. Specialists are 
thinking through its prospects. The head of the general 
machine-building design bureau, (?Aleksey Prusanov), said in an 
interview with ITAR-TASS that a feasibility study for the entire 
complex will be ready by the end of 1994. The document will 
envisage the use of initially two and subsequently five silos 
for launching light booster rockets, and the creation of two 
launchpads for heavy booster rockets. A missile division used 
to be stationed on the site where the cosmodrome is being built. 
The site will be several times smaller in size after it has been 
converted for its new purpose. The reclaimed land will be 
returned to the state. 

</TEXT>

