accuse President Kravchuk of not giving the Crimea the 
possibility to conduct reforms. Nevertheless, in the opinion of 
Mykola Mykhalchenko, in the long term, the Ukrainian president's 
decree will stabilize the political situation in both Crimea and 
Ukraine, and it serves as a serious argument in the battle with 
separatism, preventing the creation of a legal basis for 
Crimea's secession from Ukraine. 

