<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Envoy Arrives To Mediate in Dniester Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703150894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1030 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1703150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 17/3/1994 -- The special envoy 
of Russian President, Vladlen Vasev arrived last night in 
Chisinau to mediate the Dniester conflict. Tomorrow, 17 March, 
he will meet with President Snegur, who returns today from 
Brussels. A visit to Tiraspol is also scheduled for tomorrow, 
where Vasev will meet decisionmakers of the self-proclaimed 
Dniester republic. Sources from the Russian Embassy told BASA 
that Vasev will stay in Moldova for about a week. During the 
summer of 1992 military conflict Vasev was in the group of 
Russian representatives as an observer in the four-party 
mechanism for solving the conflict. On 10 March, communicating 
about the meeting in Moscow of Dniester President Igor Smirnov 
with officials from the State Duma of Russia, Tiraspol radio 
asserted that Vasev was nominated as mediator at the insistence 
of the Dniester leader. 

</TEXT>

