<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Issues Decree on Deregulation, Privatization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603145894 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 1111 GMT 16 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The president of Uzbekistan has issued a decree on 
the priorities for deregulation and privatization. Among the 
priorities are broad involvement of the population in the 
process of reforms by means of developing the securities market, 
creating public joint-stock companies with a reduction in the 
proportion of shares belonging to the state, and forming markets 
for real estate and means of production. 
  Another priority is the demonopolization of production and 
control structures and the attraction of foreign investments by 
holding tenders, auctions, investment auctions, and direct sale 
of property. The decree stresses the need for state support for 
privatized enterprises. 
  For public joint-stock companies in which the state retains 
its share, it is envisioned to have blocs of shares belonging to 
the state, to the work force, to foreign partners, and free 
selling on stock exchanges and securities markets, including 
those abroad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

