<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze on Cabinet Confirmation Procedure </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703121494 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0920 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The parliament of the Republic of Georgia reconvened 
today [17 March] and was chaired by the Deputy Speaker Vakhtang 
Rcheulishvili. [name as heard] 
  Eduard Shevardnadze, the chairman of the Georgian State 
Council and head of state addressed parliament on the procedure 
of confirming the Cabinet of Ministers to be discussed by 
parliament on Tuesday 22 March. 
  The agenda was confirmed. The first issue on the agenda was 
a resolution on high schools addressed by the Chairman of the 
Education Commission Raul Kuprava. The issue caused heated 
debates. 
  At the moment parliament is having a break. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

