<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas, EU Envoys Discuss Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703203194 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1700 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Algirdas Brazauskas and diplomats from the 
states of the European Union accredited in Vilnius held an 
informal discussion concerning Lithuania and the European Union 
[words indistinct]. During a working lunch at the Draugyste 
Hotel, preparation of the draft treaty on free trade between 
Lithuania and the European Union and the possibility of 
accelerating the signing of the treaty on Lithuania's associate 
membership -- the European Treaty -- was discussed. 
  The president again stressed Lithuania's aspiration to 
integrate into the European security, economic and political 
structures. 
  Petras Vaitiekunas, the president's adviser on foreign 
policy, who was present at the meeting, said that the 
ambassadors noted that Lithuania is in possession of the key out 
of Europe. According to the adviser the diplomats from the 
European states stressed that a civilized regulation of 
relations between Lithuania and Poland will be regarded by 
Europe very positively, and that Europe would welcome the 
signing of the interstate treaty. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

