<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportedly Kills 6 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903135494 Paris AFP in English 1328 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 19 (AFP) -- At least six people were 
killed and 56 others were wounded Saturday in an explosion in a 
metro station in the Azerbaijani capital Baku, the Azeri news 
agency Assa Irada said. The agency said the blast was a 
"terrorist" action, although no further details were immediately 
available. 
  For more than five years Azerbaijan has been fighting a 
bloody war with Armenian separatists over the disputed enclave 
of Nagorno-Karabakh in south western Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

