<H3> <TI>   Ministry Accuses Armenia of Renewing Hostilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803142194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1331 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sevindzh Abdullayeva, Viktor </F>
Shulman] 
  [Text] Baku, 18 Mar -- After the short period of calm that 
followed the meeting of the heads of parliament of Azerbaijan 
and Armenia, the Armenian side has again started military 
operations. According to the reports from Azerbaijan's Ministry 
of Defense that have come in today, they resumed on Thursday 
after the shelling of Azerbaijan Army positions in the direction 
of Agdam from a "Grad" missile installation, which did not stop 
for 24 hours. 
  The same source informs of a concentration of forces and 
equipment by the enemy on other sections of the front. 

</TEXT>

