<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Fighting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903170394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1551 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As Interfax learned at the press service of the 
Nagorno-Karabakh Defense Army, a relative calm on the Karabakh 
front established in recent days was violated on Saturday 
morning. 
  According to the press service, concentration of Azeri 
troops 
on the southeastern part of the front undertook an offensive in 
the direction of the regional center Fizuli. However, by the 
afternoon Nagorno-Karabakh defense units managed to repel all 
attacks of the Azeri Army inflicting it considerable losses. 
  As of 15:00 fighting on that part of the front continued. 
There have been no major changes in other parts of the front. 
  In the meantime, the Azeri Defense Ministry reports that 
yesterday Armenian artillery shelled Azeri positions in the 
Fizuli and Agdam parts of the front. There have been no 
casualties. Damage is being estimated. 

</TEXT>

