<H3> <TI>   Ministry on Attack, Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003183994 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2003183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of Azerbaijan Ministry of Defense press service </F>
communique on 20 March] 
  [Text] Enemy units, which [words indistinct], launched a 
strong three-pronged attack on our positions early on 19 March. 
The attacks were launched from Goradiz district, [placename 
indistinct], which was occupied, and [words indistinct]. The 
enemy units also attacked from the direction of Kurapatkino and 
tried to penetrate our defenses. Serious clashes are taking 
place in that part of the front line. Azerbaijan's military 
forces are trying to defend their homeland on the eve of the 
Novruz Festival. The enemy has suffered many casualties. The 
enemy units have lost more than 100 troops, five tanks, and an 
infantry combat vehicle in that battlefield. The Armenians have 
been forced to retreat along the entire front line. 
  Meanwhile, various areas along Azerbaijan's border with 
Armenia have been fired on by various types of arms from that 
Republic's territory. 

</TEXT>

