<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Sends Condolences to Rafsanjani on Crash </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003144694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1334 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2003144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijan's President Geydar Aliyev has lamented 
the death of 19 passengers and 13 members of the crew of the 
Iranian C-130 cargo jet which crashed on March 18 several 
kilometers away from Nagorno-Karabakh's capital Stepanakert. 
  In a telephone conversation on March 19 the Azeri leader 
briefed Iranian President 'Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani on what 
Baku knew about the air crash. 
  The two presidents stressed the need for an in-depth 
investigation into the circumstances of the crash. They felt an 
investigation must be carried out on the site of the tragic 
incident. 

</TEXT>

