<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Department Seeks Official; Arrests Wife </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903110694 Yerevan SNARK in English 1500 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, March 18 (SNARK)--The Armenia's Office of 
Prosecutor has decided to arrest Vahan Avakyan, the first deputy 
of the Chief Adviser of the Armenian president on questions of 
national security. David Shahnazaryan, the acting chief of the 
Armenia's State Department of National Security, said that on 
March 15 in the Yerevan airport "Zvartnots" Zaruyi Yavuryan, the 
wife of Avakyan had been arrested when she tried to take out 
from the republic 6 floppy diskettes and documents with the 
secret information, which was, according to the official 
resolution, state secret. 
  Vahan Avakyan, who was in Moscow in that time, refused to 
return to Armenia, when the president apparat called him back. 
Some time later he connected with the president apparat by 
telephone and said that he was out of the CIS and was under 
protection of a foreign country. 
  According to Shahnazaryan, they instituted proceeding on 
these facts. Ashot Manucharyan, the former Chief Adviser of the 
Armenian president on National security, acts as a witness in 
this case but he refused to give any testimony. On 
Shahnazaryan's words, taking into account the publications in 
the Bulgarian press, Vahan Avakyan is in Bulgaria now. 
"Armenian officially asked Bulgaria's authorities about that 
but hasn't received any explanation yet." Shahnazaryan said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

