<H3> <TI>   Special Stockholding, Commercial Bank Set Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003165394 Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network in Russian 0215 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Islam Karimov, president of the Republic of 
Uzbekistan issued a decree on the formation of a special 
(stockholding) and commercial bank to assist with trading and 
commercial activities. The document states that with the aim of 
meeting the requirements of the population in goods and 
replenishing the home market and also for providing financial 
support to [word indistinct] and further developing trade in the 
Republic, a special stockholding and commercial bank called 
Saudagar [Trader] to promote trade and commerce be formed. Its 
main activities will be to serve the trading organizations of 
Uzbekistan, carry out commodity circulation, engage in trading 
and purchasing operations, and [words indistinct] between 
trading organizations and enterprises in other fields of the 
economy. 
  The founders of the Saudagar bank will be the Finance 
Ministry, the Central Bank, the Uzbeksauda [Uzbek trade] 
Association, [name indistinct], Uzbekbirlashu [Uzbek 
Association], and the National Bank for Foreign Economic 
Activities of the Republic of Uzbekistan. The full text of the 
this decree will be published in the press. 

</TEXT>

