<F P=103> LD1903111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President of Kazakhstan Nursultan Nazarbayev met 
U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry in Alma-Ata [Almaty] 
today. The head of the U.S. military department told journalists 
after the meeting that President Bill Clinton had charged him 
with paying particular attention in Alma-Ata to the 
implementation of programmes agreed during the recent visit by 
President Nazarbayev to the United States. This concerns 
primarily the deepening reinforcement of military cooperation 
between the two countries, assistance to Kazakhstan on 
conversion, research into the Semipalatinsk testing ground to 
establish the extent of the damage, and providing for medical 
assistance to the inhabitants of the Semipalatinsk region. 

