<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Enterprises on Sale by Privatization Investment Coupon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803144094 Almaty KAZTAG in Russian 1600 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty KAZTAG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- The State Property 
Committee has named 50 enterprises that will be offered for sale 
in the first ever specialized coupon auction. The list of 
enterprises was published in the republican newspapers YEGEMEN 
KAZAKHSTAN [SOVEREIGN] and KAZAKHSTANSKAYA PRAVDA. These facts 
were given at a news conference held by Zhanibek Karibzhanov, 
chairman of the State Property Committee. 
  He stressed that a new, very important stage of 
implementation of the massive scale privatization program is 
beginning for investment funds and for floated enterprises, 
which will be sold at these coupon auctions. Practically all 
inhabitants of the Republic -- 96.5 percent -- have already 
received their privatization check books. A new deadline was 
set and check books will continue to be handed out until 1 April. 
  The first auction will be held on 29 April with the 
participation of 109 investment funds with licences from the 
State Property Committee. Their applications for participation 
will be taken on 28 April from 1500 until 1800 local time. The 
starting price for a share of each of the 50 enterprises will be 
announced by the state committee no later than 5 April. Among 
objects to be put to tender: Profitable light industry 
enterprises, large construction industry, and processing 
industry from the various regions of the Republic will be sold. 
  Similar coupon auctions, starting from May, will be held 
every two weeks. Until the end of the year, at 17 auctions, 
shares of 1,200 enterprises are planned to be sold for 
privatization investment coupons, and shares of 2,500 
enterprises -- by the end of 1995. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

