<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakhmonov Attends Regional Executive Chairmen Seminar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803135994 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A republic seminar-conference of chairmen of 
executive committees of the local soviets of people's deputies 
continues its work in Dushanbe. Its participants met the 
members of the presidium of the Supreme Council of the Republic 
of Tajikistan, yesterday. 
  The issues relating to the population's social security 
during the period of transition to a market economy, financial 
and economic activities of the executive committees, and the 
strengthening of material and technical bases of the local 
soviets were discussed. 
  Emomali Rakhmonov, the head of state and chairman of the 
Supreme Council of Tajikistan met the participants of the 
seminar-conference yesterday afternoon. He pointed out that the 
specific tasks of the local soviets were determined in the 
republican meeting that took place in Dushanbe on 25 February 
1994. That is why, he pointed out, everyone has to resolve 
issues relating to a way out of the economic crisis and the 
successful implementation of the spring sowing. 
  Similarly, issues relating to the repatriation of refugees, 
creation of new working seats, provision of food for the 
population, and other vital problems were examined during the 
course of the meeting. 
  Rakhmonov said that the working commission has completed the 
work on the draft of the new Tajik constitution and asks the 
participants of the seminar-conference to express their opinion 
on ways of adopting the new constitution, holding the referendum 
on determining the form of state administration, and election of 
the new parliament. 
  The head of state answered numerous questions from the 
chairmen of town and rayon executive committees. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

