<H3> <TI>   Official Dismissed for Embezzlement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803161294 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2125 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1803161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Comrat, BASAPRESS 17/3/1994 -- From our 
correspondent: The government of the self-proclaimed Gagauz 
Republic has dismissed the head of economy, finance and state 
inspection direction "for serious financial violations." 
Reliable sources told BASAPRESS that 160 million rubles were 
embezzled from the credits granted by the "Gagauzcombanc" to the 
economic entities and was later illegally invested in 
transactions. The budget of Gagauz Republic for 1994 was a 
problem of major dispute, because the localities densely 
inhabited by Gagauzians do not want to take part in its 
formation. The Gagauz government decided that the economic 
entities in this region should make allocations to the budget 
"within the necessary limits." Local observers say that the 
Republic became almost insolvent; it does not have budget 
sources. 

</TEXT>

