<H3> <TI>   Danish Military Delegation Arrives in Chisinau </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1903204194 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1830 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1903204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 17/3/1994 -- Invited by the 
Moldovan Ministry of Defence, an official delegation of Denmark 
arrived yesterday in Chisinau. It is led by Army General Iorgen 
Lyng, supreme commander of the Danish Armed Forces, the Ministry 
of Defence press secretariat reports. The schedule includes 
meetings with Moldovan Minister of Defence Pavel Creanga, 
General Headquarters Chief Pavel Chirau, Premier Andrei 
Sangheli, acting Minister of Foreign Affairs Ion Botnaru. A 
series of common interest problems will be discussed. According 
to the quoted source, Moldovan officials will ask for the 
support of Danish representatives within NATO, especially in the 
problem of the 14th Army withdrawal. Tomorrow, the military 
delegation is to return to Denmark, the press secretariat noted. 

</TEXT>

