<H3> <TI>   Premier Flies To Sochi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003224794 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 2155 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The POSTFAKTUM agency reports that rumors are being 
circulated in Moscow that on 20 March Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin urgently flew to Sochi to meet the president, that 
telephones in the House of the Russian Federation Government on 
Krasnopresnenskaya Naberezhnaya are receiving only incoming 
calls and it is impossible to phone from the White House, and 
that special purpose units were put on red alert and can enter 
Moscow any minute. The source was connecting the emergence of 
these rumors with the alleged aggravation of Boris Yeltsin's 
health. However, in Viktor Chernomyrdin's reception office and 
the Russian Federation Government press service, this 
information was categorically refuted. 
  Answering a question by the POSTFAKTUM agency correspondent 
as to whether special purpose units have been put on red alert, 
a duty officer at the interior troops headquarters said that 
nothing of the kind had happened and nothing of the kind is 
expected. 

</TEXT>

