<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Schedule `Fairly Tight' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103130094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1143 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin goes out on car ride 
or takes walks when he is not working, officials in his 
entourage told Interfax. In particular, he took a walk in the 
vicinity of Elbrus last week-end. 
  The sources said that Yeltsin's schedule was "fairly tight." 
Several senior administration officials, as well as Prime 
Minister Chernomyrdin, are expected Monday. 
  The exact date of Yeltsin's return to Moscow has not been 
set 
but his vacation will not exceed the originally planned two 
weeks, Interfax was told. Yeltsin left Moscow last Monday. 

