<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Chernomyrdin Meet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103173594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1722 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sochi March 21 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin vacationing on the Black Sea met with Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin on Monday to discuss a range of political 
and economic issues. 
  Among the issues discussed were implementation of the 
president's state-of-the-nation address on strengthening Russian 
statehood, the state budget and ways to reach civic accord in 
the country, the presidential press service said. 
  Special attention was paid to the preparations for the 
upcoming spring sowing campaign in Russian agricultural regions, 
as well as the situation in Georgia, Abkhazia, Nagorno-Karabakh 
and other issues. 
  After the one-to-one talks, the president and the premier 
were joined by Krasnodar regional administration head Nikolay 
Yegorov and Sochi mayor Nikolay Karpov. They agreed to set up 
working groups to work out a draft agreement on the delineation 
of powers between federal and local bodies of power as envisaged 
by the constitution and the federal treaty. 
  Yeltsin and Chernomyrdin supported the idea of holding the 
2002 Winter Olympic Games in Sochi. 

</TEXT>

