<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Denies `Coup' Involvement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103165494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1613 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 21 TASS -- Russian First Deputy Prime 
Minister Oleg Soskovets denied press reports about his 
involvement in the alleged "anti-Yeltsin coup" and asked the 
office of the prosecutor general to clear up the accusations. 
  The "OBSHCHAYA GAZETA" said in its 11th edition that a 
"group 
of state officials" planned "to oust President Boris Yeltsin" 
and listed Soskovets among them. 
  Acting Prosecutor General Alexey Ilyushenko ordered to check 
the claims, the prosecutor's office said on Monday adding that 
the Interior Ministry, [and] the Federal Counterintelligence 
Service are also engaged in the investigation. 
  It added that all measures are being taken to check whether 
the press report corresponds to reality and warned that the 
newspaper may face criminal charges "of slander combined with 
accusation of a state crime" if the report was false. 

</TEXT>

