<H3> <TI>   Court Confirms Zhirinovskiy's Election to Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1328 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803140394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 18 TASS -- The Moscow regional court 
overruled today a lower court's decision stripping Russian 
nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy of his seat in the 
State Duma. 
  The higher court annuled the decision of the district 
Shchelkovo court of February 25, which declared null and void 
the results of the parliamentary elections last year in the 
electoral district, in which Zhirinovskiy was elected to the the 
lower chamber of the Russian legislature. The court ruled that 
the decision was "inconsistent and surpassed the court's 
competency." 
  A statement issued today by Zhirinovskiy's Liberal 
Democratic 
Party press service mockingly expressed "sympathy for certain 
politicians and mass media who failed again in their campaign to 
discredit Vladimir Zhirinovskiy." 

</TEXT>

