<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide Promises Action Against `Mass Unrest' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003212394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Law enforcement bodies will use the entire arsenal 
of special means to prevent possible mass unrest in Moscow. 
This was reported by Yuriy Baturin, an aide to the Russian 
president for national security, in an interview to ITAR-TASS. 
According to him, the opposition groupings rejecting the 
Memorandum proposed by President Boris Yeltsin are preparing to 
hold major rallies and demonstrations in Moscow in May. To 
prevent a repeat of the events of May 1993, it is envisaged to 
use a number of technical contact-free means, including 
water-cannons. Yuriy Baturin stressed that in case of public 
order violations, legal mechanisms will be put into effect 
without delay, especially against those to whom the political 
amnesty was extended. 

</TEXT>

