<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian National Sobor To Be `Transformed' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903170794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1331 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Belskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 19 TASS -- The Russian National Sobor 
(Assembly) (RNS), headed by Former KGB General Aleksandr 
Sterligov, should be transformed into a political organisation 
"so that it could participate in the formation of power and 
administration bodies of the Russian Federation", speakers said 
at a meeting of the Moscow City conference of the RNS here on 
Saturday. An RNS congress is to be held in Suzdal early in 
April to adopt a charter of the organisation. 
  The conference was addressed by RNS leader Aleksandr 
Sterligov. He made an evaluation of the situation in the 
country, noting disunity among the ranks of the patriotic forces 
of Russia. 
  It follows from Sterligov's remarks the RNS has virtually 
lost all allies after the events of the Autumn last year and the 
December parliamentary elections. Sterligov pointed out the 
correctness of the RNS' principled position of nonalignment with 
respect to the National Salvation Front as well as 
non-participation in the latest elections. 

</TEXT>

