<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gas Industry Sets Up Anti-Terrorist Units </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1903125094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 19 Mar 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1903125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Gazprom Sets Up Its Own </F>
Anti-Terrorist Unit"] 
  [Text] MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned that some time 
ago, rapid reaction groups were set up at Mostransgaz and a 
number of other Gazprom branches. They are called security 
services, but their area of expertise is somewhat unusual. 
Apart from protecting shipments, people, and installations, 
they are called upon to fight terrorism at gas production 
facilities. They also guard the pipeline that pumps gas abroad. 
The bulk of the group is made up of former KGB and Internal 
Affairs Ministry staffers. They all are authorized to carry 
firearms, which, however, have never been used. Those who do 
not have the right to carry guns are now completing a crash 
course to receive a certificate required by the Internal Affairs 
Ministry authorization department. 

</TEXT>

