<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Edict on Creation of `Citizenship Department' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803165394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1346 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 18 TASS -- President Boris Yeltsin 
issued a decree on a citizenship department at the Russian 
president's office, reported the Russian president's press 
service on Friday. 
  The decree sets up the citizenship department on the basis 
of 
the former citizenship division at the president's office. The 
president appointed Abdulakh Kasbulatovich Mikitayev chief of 
the department. He will concurrently head the commission on 
citizenship at the Russian president. 
  The department's main task is to ensure the commission's 
operations in conducting a united state policy in the sphere of 
citizenship. 

</TEXT>

