<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Endorses Cutting Taxes for Producers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803143594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1252 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Magnitogorsk March 18 TASS -- "The present system of 
taxing enterprises when taxes sometimes total 80 per cent of 
revenues, must be changed," Russian First Vice-Premier Oleg 
Soskovets told journalists on Friday after a conference on how 
to make the Magnitogorsk iron and steel combine a joint stock 
society. 
  According to Soskovets, taxes should be cut down to 45 per 
cent, as is the case in civilised countries. "Tax legislation 
should stimulate production and not to pave grounds for 
concealing taxes, as is the case now," the vice-premier stressed. 
  Soskovets noted that the government plans to examine the 
question of cutting the value-added tax in the near future. He 
stressed that it is necessary to "lift customs duties from goods 
crossing borders inside the Commonwealth countries". 

</TEXT>

