<H3> <TI>   Leningrad Regional Elections May Be Invalidated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003144894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1334 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2003144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Elections to the Leningrad Regional Legislative 
Assembly held on Sunday March 20 are likely to be qualified as 
invalid, member of the Regional Electoral Commission Valentina 
Molotova told Interfax. 
  She said that by 12:00, March 20, only 114,706 people had 
come to the polling stations which is 9.32000060100f the total number 
of electors. The Regional Legislative Assembly, which is to 
approve the regional budget and pass legal acts, has 25 seats. 
The Regional Electoral Commission has registered 103 candidates. 

</TEXT>

