<H3> <TI>   Suspects Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103132994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1143 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Several people suspected of involvement in shelling 
the residence of President Jokhar Dudayev were detained in 
Groznyy, the Chechen capital, Shamsuddi Vakhidov, head of the 
anti-terrorist squad in the republic's Interior Ministry, told 
Interfax. He added that a criminal case had been launched by 
the investigation branch of the State Security Department. 
  A guided missile was fired from a nine-storey house under 
construction one kilometer away from the presidential palace 
late Saturday. No significant damage was done. Officials in 
the presidential headquarters did not confirm that the shelling 
had taken place. 

</TEXT>

