<H3> <TI>   Chechen President Replaces Top Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003182194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1719 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2003182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Dzhokhar Dudayev of Russia's separatist 
republic of Chechnya on Sunday made some major replacements in 
his civil service. He dismissed Prosecutor General Elza 
Sheripova (the post still being vacant), Interior Minister 
Salman Albakov was replaced by Magomed Eldiyev, chief of the 
Penalty Execution Department, chief of the Criminal Police 
Department Saipuddi Khasanov was replaced by his deputy 
Said-Khasan Batayev, while Akhmed Gaduyev, a district 
prosecutor, was substituted for Idris Albastov as Supreme Court 
chairman. 
  Observers do not see any connection between these 
replacements and an attack on Dudayev's residence on Saturday 
evening. 

</TEXT>

