<H3> <TI>   Urges Extended State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003111394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1058 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2003111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz March 20 TASS -- "There is now a danger 
of a new conflict in the area said North Ossetian President 
Akhsarbek Galazov, speaking at a meeting with republican leaders 
here on Sunday. Therefore, it is expedient to prolong the state 
of emergency regime in several districts of the region, expiring 
on March 31. 
  "The Russian peace-keeping force is the main security 
guarantor in the region," the president claimed. 
  There are various opinions on the state of emergency regime 
in the North Ossetian official quarters and among multinational 
population of the republic, ranging from its repeal to 
preservation and extension, provided the temporary 
administration is transformed and functions of subordinated to 
it military units are changed. 
  This issue will be debated by the North Ossetian Parliament 
next week. 

</TEXT>

