<F P=102>  LD2103102394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yuriy Biragov, chairman of the North Ossetia Supreme 
Soviet, and Georgiy Kozayev, first deputy chairman of the 
republican government, have sent a telegram on behalf of the 
Presidium of the North Ossetia Supreme Soviet to President Boris 
Yeltsin of Russia, chairman of the Federation Council Vladimir 
Shumeyko, and State Duma chairman Ivan Rybkin. The telegram 
states, inter alia, that the proposal made by a number of 
Russian deputies to introduce federal rule on the territory of 
North Ossetia has given rise to indignation among the people of 
the republic. Such proposals are regarded in North Ossetia as 
an attempt by certain forces -- I quote -- to play the national 
card on the Yugoslav model. 

