<H3> <TI>   Further on Reaction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903094694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 0900 GMT 19 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Estonian Foreign Ministry has welcomed the 
treaty initialled at the last round of Russian-Latvian talks on 
the withdrawal of Russian Armed Forces from Latvia, which 
stipulates that the troops must be withdrawn by 31 August this 
year. The Estonian Foreign Ministry also expresses the hope 
that on the basis of the proposal made by the Russian prime 
minister to withdraw troops from Estonia by 31 August, and on 
the attitude of the international community that no additional 
conditions may be attached to the withdrawal, Russia will be 
ready to initial the treaty on the withdrawal of the troops at 
the next, the 18th round of talks, which will take place in 
Moscow on 5, 6 April. 

</TEXT>

