<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Says Pact With Russia Ready To Sign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803185694 Tallinn Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press 
Release in English 1549 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1803185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press 
Release </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Immediate release" from the Estonian Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs in Tallinn: "Estonian-Russian Agreement Ready To Be 
Initialled in April in Moscow"] 
  [Text] March 18, 1994 -- The initialing of the agreement 
for the withdrawal of Russian troops from Latvia by August 31, 
1994 is viewed as a positive development by the Estonian 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs. 
  It is important to note that the agreement for the complete 
withdrawal of Russian troops from Estonia is also ready to be 
initialled. Estonia had hoped that this could have been done at 
the last round of talks, but instead the Russian side presented 
new demands and even placed the mutually agreed upon withdrawal 
date of August 31, 1994 into question. 
  In light of the Russian Prime Minister's recent stated 
agreement to remove Russian troops from Estonia by August 31, 
1994 and the international consensus that the withdrawal of 
Russian troops from Estonia can not be tied to any conditions, 
the Estonian Ministry of Foreign Affairs hopes that Russia will 
initial the agreement to withdraw troops from Estonia during the 
18th round of negotiations April 5-6 in Moscow. 
  By completing the removal of its troops from all three 
Baltic 
States by August 31, 1994, Russia will finally be in conformance 
with paragraph 15 of the 1992 Helsinki document, which requires 
"early, orderly and complete" withdrawal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16802 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov054_t_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-054 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

