<H3> <TI>   Ulmanis Holds News Conference on Visit to Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803164094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1400 GMT 18 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] This afternoon the Latvian President Guntis 
Ulmanis and representatives of the government cabinet returned 
to Riga from Italy, having discussed on their two-day official 
visit future co-operation between the two countries. From Riga 
airport, where a news conference took place, our correspondent 
Ainars Asaks has returned. Let's listen to the president's 
brief assessment of the visit. 
  [Begin Ulmanis recording] This was my first visit this year 
outside the country's borders, and I regard the visit as 
successful. We are satisfied with the results of our work. For 
two days we were in two states: Italy and the Vatican. The 
first purpose of this visit was to create mutual understanding 
between Italy and Latvia, the Vatican and Latvia. In the two 
days we met both the Italian president and the foreign minister 
and Foreign Ministry representatives. On the second day there 
was to my mind a very important reception at the Vatican. With 
great sympathy, with great support, the Pope very attentively 
listened to the problems that are current in Latvia. The 
parties to the talks (?assessed) Latvian- Russian relations. 
Although the Pope did not promise anything, nevertheless, I 
understand from what he said that he regards Latvia and the 
Baltic lands as very important geopolitically for the 
development of this region, which could be a golden key in the 
formation of relations between East and West. [end recording] 
  After the withdrawal of the Russian troops, Italian-Latvian 
relations will become more stable, emphasized Foreign Minister 
Georgs Andrejevs at the news conference. 
  [Begin Andrejevs recording] On questions of a general 
nature, 
there was of course interest in how Italian-Latvian relations 
could develop in the future. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

