<H3> <TI>   Panel To Facilitate Possible EU Membership Meets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2103104294 Tallinn BNS in English 1312 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2103104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 19, BNS -- A work group set up to make 
preparations for Estonia's possible membership in the European 
Union [EU] met in Tallinn Friday [18 March] to draw up a 
tentative timetable for discussion of the outcome of panel 
meetings under the group. 
  Each of the different panels under the work group has to 
present by March 31 a report on the predicted changes that may 
take place in connection with the country's joining the EU, a 
representative at the Foreign Ministry press office said. 
  The meetings are to estimate whether the predicted changes 
will be in line with Estonia's current principles and directions 
of development. Also to be assessed is the volume of work to be 
done in preparing for the membership, its costs, and how to get 
experts from different fields involved in the project. 

</TEXT>

