<H3> <TI>   Russia Refuses To Respond To Spying Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803150994 Tallinn BNS in English 1042 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1803150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 18, BNS -- The Russian embassy in 
Tallinn says it is unnecessary to publicly respond to anonymous 
charges of spying moved against Anatoliy Chizhikov, a counsellor 
at the embassy. 
  "We do not consider it necessary to publicly respond to such 
provocative actions by anonymous authors. But speaking about 
the Russian diplomat concerned, he received the agreement from 
the Estonian government for being accredited in the Republic of 
Estonia in his capacity as military, air force and naval attache 
with the Russian embassy in Tallinn," said Andrey Yakushev, 
press attache at the embassy. 
  Estonia's Eesti Aeg weekly newspaper in its Wednesday's [16 
March] edition published an unsigned paper saying that Anatoliy 
Chizhikov is the "chief Russian spy in Estonia." Anonymous 
authors of the note claim the diplomat "coordinates the activity 
of the Russian spying center operating in Estonia," as well as 
of a "special intelligence group" which includes employees from 
the Estonian Defense Ministry, the Central Staff, the Interior 
and Foreign ministries, as well as other government departments. 

</TEXT>

