<H3> <TI>   Laar Reassures on Russian Airfield </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103151694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1400 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prime Minister Mart Laar said today during the 
Riigikogu information hour that beginning in March of last year 
Estonian border guards began partially controlling the aircraft 
landing at and taking off from Amari Airfield, which is under 
Russian military control. Laar stated that the export of goods 
and illegal border crossings via Amari are no longer possible 
because Russian servicemen must first obtain permission from the 
Estonian Defense Ministry for flights. He rejected claims that 
criminal forces are using Amari to export cars. According to 
information available to Laar, five Russian military transport 
planes have landed and taken off at Amari during the first 
months of the year, having been first cleared by the Estonian 
border guards. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

