<F P=102>  WS1803185294 Tallinn BNS in English 1357 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1803185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tallinn, Mar 18, BNS -- Estonian Defense Police 
Chief Juri Pihl said that the representative of the Russian 
Liberal Democratic Party in Estonia, Pyotr Rozhok, needs to be 
examined by a psychiatrist. 
  Pihl's remarks followed after his department on Wednesday 
[16 
March] formally brought charges against Rozhok. 
  "If a person doesn't go there (to a psychiatrist) by his own 
will, bringing under compulsion must be implemented. The same 
will be done if Rozhok won't appear before investigators. 
Everything will be done according to the laws and Rozhok has 
the possibility to take a lawyer," Pihl said. 
  The representative of Russian radical nationalist leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's misleadingly-named Liberal Democratic 
Party in his speech in Narva on Jan. 25 and in an interview with 
the Russian-language SILLAMAESKI VESTNIK local newspaper of the 
northeast Estonian town of Sillamae "fanned inter-ethnic and 
political hostility," the indictment says. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

