<H3> <TI>   Registration of Paldiski Residents To Commence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2103104894 Tallinn ETA in English 0841 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2103104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From 19 March PUHAPAEVALEHT, p 6; "News Bulletin" No. 54/94] </F>
  [Text] Monday, March 21 -- The government intends to start 
registering residents of Paldiski by the end of March. The 
residents are to fill in special questionnaires and have their 
passports stamped. The move was made necessary by the refusal 
of the Russian military authorities to hand over the militia 
registration files. The registration is to concern the Russian 
military as well. 
  The joint Estonian-Russian staff exercise concerned the 
evacuation of the nuclear fuel from Paldiski and also studied 
the "black scenario" connected with possible escape of 
radioactive material. The Estonian side has agreed that 200 
additional Russian experts with equipment be allowed to arrive 
in case of emergency. 

</TEXT>

