<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE Approves Initialling Treaty With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803145294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1300 GMT 18 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the plenary session of the permanent commission 
of the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe on 
Thursday [17 March] in Vienna, the initialling of the bilateral 
agreement between Latvia and Russia on the withdrawal of the 
Russian Army was assessed. In the name of the European Union, 
Greece expressed satisfaction at the fact that the 31 August 
this year is to be observed as the deadline for the withdrawal 
of the Russian Army, adding that it awaits the ratification of 
the treaty by the two countries' parliaments. Sweden, Finland, 
and Poland expressed approval of what has been achieved, and 
emphasized the interest of the CSCE in these issues. The 
representative of the United States of America also expressed 
his support for what was achieved at the bilateral 
Latvian-Russian talks, and emphasized that the support of the 
CSCE in Europe on the issue of the Skrunda radar station is very 
important to the U.S. Government. 

</TEXT>

