<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jursenas, Olechowski Welcome Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903091994 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2200 GMT 18 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following talks that lasted nearly two years, 
Lithuania and Poland have initialled a bilateral treaty on good 
neighborliness and cooperation. Upon initialling the treaty in 
Warsaw on Friday [18 March] the Lithuanian and Polish foreign 
ministers stressed that the treaty was of vital importance to 
both sides while [words indistinct]. According to Polish 
Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski the treaty opened a new page 
in bilateral relations between Lithuania and Poland. Lithuanian 
Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys said that some time would still 
be required to understand the importance of this document. 
  The text of the treaty will be made public as soon as it is 
signed by the presidents of the two states. The signing of the 
document is expected to take place in [word indistinct] April. 

</TEXT>

