<H3> <TI>   Pulokas Signs Disaster Aid Pact in Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2103100494 Vilnius ELTA in English 1942 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2103100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 460] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, March 18, ELTA -- Deputy Defence Minister 
Gediminas Pulokas returned from Bonn on Friday [18 March]. 
  He signed Lithuanian-German agreement on mutual help in 
cases 
of calamities. The agreement also provides for main volunteer 
aid conditions which encompass sending rescue groups, experts 
and aid materials. 
  The main directions of the cooperation were discussed during 
the meeting of representatives of the both sides which was held 
on March 16. Lithuanians were invited to participate in the 
joint civilian security training exercises which will be held at 
the beginning of May. 

