<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sweden Allocates Funds for Ignalina Safety </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803134694 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1000 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swedish state nuclear energy inspection has 
acquired funds that will be destined to ensure the safety of the 
Ignalina nuclear power station. 
  The Swedish Government yesterday allocated for this purpose 
17 million kroner from the budget of the foreign affairs 
department. Another 10 million kroner has been allocated by the 
nature protection department. A control service taking care of 
the safety of the nuclear power station is to be formed in 
Lithuania. A part of the Swedish fund will be used for this 
service's needs. 

</TEXT>

