<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Pro-Russian Bloc Founded in Crimea </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003103494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0930 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The political bloc "Sevastopol-Crimea-Russia," which 
has been founded in Sevastopol, is in favor of Crimea's close 
political and economic unity with Russia, and has as its slogan 
"Our homeland is Russia" [Nasha rodina -- Rossiya]. Aleksandr 
Kruglov, a Crimean people's deputy, who has been elected the 
leader of the new association, told a RIA correspondent this by 
phone. According to Kruglov, the "Sevastopol-Crimea-Russia" 
bloc supports the Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov and his decree 
on holding a referendum on the Republic of Crimea's independence 
among the peninsula's population on 27 March. 

</TEXT>

