<H3> <TI>   Duma Receives State Budget for 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103093894 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
0900 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The State Duma has received the 1994 draft budget. 
Aleksandr Pochinok, deputy chairman of the budget committee, 
said there are no major divergences from the original version. 
The deficit has risen from 61.2 trillion rubles to 62.4 
trillion. This is due to a minor increase in the budget's 
expenditure allocations. Aleksandr Pochinok noted that the 
budget is fairly tough and the deficit is completely acceptable. 
At the same time he stressed that the government is again 
trying, via budgetary laws, to change the tax legislation. 

</TEXT>

