<H3> <TI>   Party Official on `Recognition' of Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903105494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1500 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, March 18 (SNARK)--Russia must become the 
guarantee of recognition of the republic of Nagorno-Karabakh, 
Nikolay Lysenko, the chairman of the National-Republican Party 
of Russia, said today in Yerevan. Commenting the results of the 
visit to Stepanakert, Lysenko said "According to the 
international regulations Karabakh has a right to establish 
sovereign republic." 
  On his words Armenia, Russia, Karabakh are connected by 
geographical strategic interests. He said "the policy, pursued 
by Turkey in Transcaucasia, must be considered as directed 
against Russia. The aggression of Azerbaijan against Karabakh 
wouldn't be possible if Turkey didn't support Azerbaijan." 
According to him there are a few people in the State Duma that 
agree with national-republicans in the question concerning to 
Armenia and Karabakh. Today the delegation of 
National-republican party leave for Moscow. 

</TEXT>

