<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Statement on Middle East </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903135694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1343 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow March 19 TASS - The Russian Foreign Ministry 
released the following statement on Saturday. 
  "On March 18 the U.N. Security Council adopted a resolution 
denouncing the massacre in Hebron and providing for a set of 
measures to ensure the safety of Palestinian civilians in the 
occupied territories. 
  "Russia, from the very beginning of the discussion of the 
resolution in the Security Council, had been calling for its 
soonest possible adoption, considering it as a crucial step for 
normalising the situation in the Middle East and resuming 
Arab-Israeli talks. 
  "The initiating steps taken by the Russian cosponsor -- 
personal address by President Boris Yeltsin to the leaders of 
Israel and the PLO, a trip by the foreign minister to Israel and 
Tunisia, a series of contacts by Russian special representatives 
in the region and energetic efforts in the Security Council -- 
not only facilitated the adoption of an effective resolution, 
but also laid the foundation for further progress in the Middle 
East peace process. 
  "Russia, together and parallelly with the American 
cosponsor, 
intends to continue the active political line in the Middle 
East, including in accordance with the provisions of the adopted 
resolution and is ready to do its best to implement the U.N. 
Security Council resolution on Hebron, as well as promote the 
soonest possible agreement between Israel and Palestinians and 
its fulfillment. This would provide opportunities in other 
directions of the Arab-Israeli dialogue and near the time of 
establishing a comprehensive and lasting peace in the Middle 
East." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

