<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to UN on Moves to Lift Iraq Oil Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803210394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1907 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] United Nations March 18 TASS -- Russia raised the 
question of lifting oil embargo against Iraq at today's 
closed-door consultative meeting of the United Nations Security 
Council, which discussed sanctions against Baghdad. 
  "Russia said that certain positive changes have recently 
occurred in Baghdad actions which testify to its intention to 
fulfill disarmament aspects of Resolution 687 and long-term 
control measures of Resolution 715," Russian permanent 
representative to the United Nations Yuliy Vorontsov told 
ITAR-TASS today. 
  In the words of Vorontsov, "the Russian delegation thinks 
that positive changes in the Iraqi stand should be encouraged". 
Bearing this in mind, Russia suggested to include in a 
statement of the Security Council president a provision on 
positive changes in Iraqi actions. 
  The Russian delegation also voiced the need for the "soonest 
agreement on the date to begin the fulfilment of long-term 
monitoring plans and duration of the 'control period' for 
estimation of its efficiency. 
  "If upon the completion of this period, say six months, 
Iraqi 
honest comprehensive fulfilment of obligations is confirmed, 
Russia will be ready to discuss the lift of oil embargo in 
accordance with paragraph 22 of Resolution 687". 
  The Russian delegation thinks Iraq should immediately 
recognize sovereignty and borders of Kuwait. 

</TEXT>

