<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovsky Postpones Visit to Czech Republic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903070894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0601 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Prague, March 19 (TASS) -- Vladimir Zhirinovsky has 
postponed his visit to the czech capital for an indefinite time, 
the CTK NEWS AGENCY reported. The visit was to begin on Sunday. 
  At the beginning of the week, when staying in Warsaw, the 
chairman of the Liberal-Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR) 
announced plans to make a two-day visit to the Czech Republic. 
However, the party leader "probably made a mistake", an LDPR 
spokesman told CTK. As it turns out, it is necessary for 
Zhirinovsky to address intra- party affairs, which will require 
his presence in Moscow on Sunday and Monday. 
  A decision to postpone the visit was taken after LDPR 
representatives' consultations with the staff of the Czech 
Embassy in Moscow. 
  Earlier Prague had made it clear that it considers 
Zhirinovsky's planned visit as highly undesirable. In 
particular, Czech Interior Minister Jan Ruml stated an intention 
to make every possible step to prevent the LDPR leader from 
visiting the country. 

</TEXT>

