<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage of Iranian Plane Crash in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<H4>   AZERTAC Reports Plane `Accident' </H4>
<F P=102> NC1803134994 Baku AZERTAC in Azeri 1148 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1803134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, 18 Mar (AZERTAC)--An Iranian Airlines Company 
transport plane flying from Moscow to Tehran was involved in an 
accident over Khankendi [Stepanakert] Rayon at about midnight 
(2330 Baku time) [1930 GMT] on 17 March. 
  According to the preliminary information given to an AZERTAC 
correspondent by the "Azerbaijani Airlines" state concern, the 
plane left Georgian airspace and entered Armenian airspace. It 
deviated from its established path and reached the Dakhlyk 
[Mountainous] Karabakh zone of Azerbaijan. It has been 
ascertained that the transport plane crashed 3 km from Khankendi. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

