<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage of Iranian Plane Crash in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<H4>   Yerevan Involvement Denied </H4>
<F P=102> NC1803201494 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1803201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zhirair Liparityan, Armenian first deputy foreign 
minister, made a statement to reporters today in connection with 
the [Iranian] plane crash. Mr. Liparityan said: 
  [Begin Liparityan recording] You might have already heard 
that last night an Iranian C-130 aircraft flying from Moscow to 
Tehran deviated by some 100 km from its established path for 
unknown reasons after crossing Georgian airspace. It did not 
enter the Armenian zone. It appears that it entered Azerbaijani 
airspace and then was involved in an accident 14 km from 
Stepanakert. It is not clear what happened. The only thing we 
know is that at around 2200 Tbilisi informed our air traffic 
controllers that the plane would enter Armenian airspace at 
2208. But, in fact it did not. A search started after that. 
The accident involving the Iranian aircraft took place at 
around 2230. Even this is not clear. In addition to the crew, 
civilians were also on board. The exact number is not clear. 
There should have been 13 crewmen. There were also others. 
[words indistinct] Probably some 30, 31 people. 
  We had no direct involvement with this incident because the 
plane was not in contact with us. But we are already providing 
every assistance to the Iranian Embassy and Government to 
facilitate the solution of the problems arising from this 
incident. I can only add that there is clear information that 
plane was experiencing technical difficulties; defects, 
technical defects. 
  This is all we know. And no one can say anything more 
definite than this. 
  Sorry, I will not reply to your questions today. Everything 
we know for certain I conveyed to you. Thank you. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

