<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communique Issued </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903093794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1707 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] St.Petersburg, 18 Mar -- The resolution on 
recommended legislative acts regulating economic relations 
within the framework of the CIS Economic Union will serve to 
implement the Treaty on setting up the CIS Economic Union. This 
is stressed in a communique on the plenary setting of the 
Interparliamentary Assembly which ended today. 
  The participants in the sitting agreed with the proposal to 
draw up a model criminal code and a model code of criminal 
procedure and to speed up the preparation of legislative acts to 
fight crime in the CIS. Stressing the urgency of maintaining 
and recreating on new foundations a single educational and 
culture space within the framework of the CIS, the Assembly 
recommended that national parliaments adopt measures for the 
development of cooperation. A recommendation was approved to 
raise the social status of pupils in the system of education and 
science, and to join the UNESCO convention "Agreement on the 
importation of materials of an educational, scientific and 
cultural nature". It was found expedient to draw up a 
recommended act for keeping internal waters in CIS ecologically 
safe. Measures were defined to prepare for the celebration of 
victory in the 1941-1945 Great Patriotic War. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

