<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Guards, Opposition Clash on Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003090694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0811 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 20 Mar -- During the night there was a big 
clash between Russian border troops and Tajik opposition 
fighters in one of the sectors of the Pyanj border detachment. 
According to military sources, intruders, whose numbers were 
not established, attempted to cross from Afghanistan into 
Tajikistan with weapons and ammunition. Their attempt did not 
succeed, and abandoning their loads and leaving several dead, 
the fighters returned to the other side of the border. There 
are no casualties among the Russian border troops. 
  According to the Russian military, the past 24 hours have 
been relatively quiet in the other sectors of the Tajik-Afghan 
border. Military equipment and subunits of fighters are being 
concentrated along the border in the northern provinces of 
Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

