<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, IMF Mission Sign Memorandum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803131794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1100 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1803131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, the final round of negotiations between the 
Belarusian Government and the IMF mission was held with the 
participation of Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich. 
The discussion focused on the issues of carrying out economic 
reforms in Belarus and the role of the IMF in their 
implementation. The strategic goals of supporting the 
continuous, effective improvement of the Belarusian economy, and 
increasing people's living standards were specified in the 
signed memorandum of mutual understanding between the government 
and the IMF. The strategy of the program is mainly based on the 
renewal of macroeconomic stability, economy, the strengthening 
of market tendencies including a decrease in inflation, the 
recovery of balance of payments, and protection of the weakest 
groups of the population during the transition period. At the 
meeting, an agreement was reached to open a permanent IMF 
mission and nominate its chairman. The opening of this mission 
is planned for July 1994. 

</TEXT>

