<H3> <TI>   Surveys Kuban Territory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903124594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1224 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1903124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchyogoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi March 19 TASS -- President Boris Yeltsin, 
Krasnodar Territorial Administration Chief Nikolay Yegorov and 
Sochi Administration Chief Nikolay Karpov flew over the south 
western areas of Kuban territory on Friday in a helicopter. They 
also surveyed the border area of Russia, the water areas of 
Novorossiisk and Tuapse ports, rice plantations, vineyards, and 
health resort complexes of Anapa and Sochi, a spokesman in the 
press service of the Sochi City Administration told ITAR-TASS on 
Saturday. 
  Most pressing problems of territorial development were 
discussed after the long flight. The president devoted special 
attention to matters connected with the accommodation of Russian 
Army units in those regions. 
  Migration problems, the development of inter-ethnic 
relations 
in the territory and various aspects of action to fight crime 
were discussed as well. The president instructed that the 
entire package of these matters be prepared to be discussed by 
Russia's Security Council session. 
  During the survey of the Tuapse and Novorossiisk ports, a 
programme for the development of the entire transportation 
complex of southern regions of Russia was discussed. 
  The president issued a number of instructions concerning the 
preservation of land reclamation systems in Kuban. A decision 
was taken to draft a special decree concerning the development 
of the children's health resort of Anapa. 

</TEXT>

