<H3> <TI>   Ministry Welcomes Accord on Troop Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803144394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1339 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Albert Maloverian] </F>

    [Text] Tallinn March 18 TASS -- The Estonian Foreign 
Ministry 
welcomes the agreement on terms, date and procedure of Russia's 
troop withdrawal from Latvia, the Estonian Foreign Ministry said 
in a statement for the press on Friday. 
  A draft agreement between Russia and Estonia was prepared 
for 
the 17th round of bilateral negotiations, "but Russia was not 
ready to sign it," the statement said. 
  According to the Estonian Foreign Ministry, the Russian 
troop 
pull-out should not be linked to any additional terms. Estonia 
expresses the hope that "Russia will be ready to initial the 
agreement at the next round of talks, due to be held in Moscow 
from April 5 to 6. 

