<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Bulletin" No. 54/94] </F>
  [Text] Monday, March 21 -- The Defence Ministry does not 
intend to order ammunition from local firms, ministry 
vice-chancellor Tarmo Milder announced. He added that state 
orders will depend on quality and price of the ammunition and 
mentioned $0.17 cartridge as an acceptable price. South 
African, Israeli, Chinese and South Korean enterprises have 
offered their cooperation to the Defence Ministry. 

