<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Defends Joint Exercise With U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1803161394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 18 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1803161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement from Russian Federation Defense Ministry </F>
Information and Press Directorate under "From Informed Sources" 
rubric: "Let Us Not Dramatize"] 
  [Text] On 16 March 1994, PRAVDA published an article by 
Major General Viktor Chudov, retired, entitled "Our Strategists 
Are Too Unsophisticated." In the article he discussed the 
forthcoming Russo-U.S. joint exercises. The article contained a 
series of gross distortions. The author of the article, who 
does not have true information on the planned exercises, casts 
doubt on the military-political expediency of them and, at the 
same time, of the whole range of Russo-U.S. relations in the 
military sphere. 
  The publication distorts the scale and nature of the planned 
exercises. In particular, the author asserts that the U.S. 3d 
Infantry Division and the Russian Armed Forces 27th Motorized 
Rifle Division are being drafted into this event in their full 
complement. In fact the plan is not to stage troop exercises 
involving all the personnel of the two divisions together with 
their combat hardware and weapons but merely a command and staff 
exercise with a very limited number of personnel (up to 250 men 
per side) and vehicles. 
  Parts of the forthcoming exercise will indeed be rehearsed 
at 
the Totskiy test range. This is due to the fact that the 27th 
Motorized Rifle Division is stationed in the area of the test 
range and a center for training peacekeeping forces, the only 
one of its kind in the Russian Armed forces at present, has been 
created here. 
  As for the cost of holding the exercise, the United States 
is 
prepared to bear that in full (up to $2 million). For the 
Russian side this is a planned exercise and does not entail any 
additional costs. 
  The main aim of this joint measure is to rehearse questions 
of cooperation in the performance of peacekeeping operations. 
The forthcoming command and staff exercise should make a real 
contribution to the cause of international cooperation in the 
settlement of conflicts in trouble spots and to the preservation 
of world peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

