<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord To Restart Nuclear Power Plant Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103145894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1432 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan March 21 TASS -- Russian Vice-Premier Oleg 
Soskovets and Armenian Premier Grant Bagratyan have signed an 
accord on restarting the Armenian nuclear power plant. 
  Under the accord, the parties will conduct a joint 
examination of the main units of the plant and put them into 
operation, after taking additional measures to ensure its safe 
functioning. They will also train operational and technical 
maintenance personnel for the plant. 
  Russia will deliver nuclear fuel to the station, help the 
plant operators and assist in setting up Armenian bodies of 
control over nuclear materials and the nuclear power engineering 
network. 
  For its part, Armenia will introduce the rules and standards 
now in use at the Russian nuclear power plants and take steps to 
secure physical safety of the plant. 
  Under the agreement, Armenia pledges not to use the nuclear 
and non-nuclear materials received from Russia, as well as the 
nuclear and non-nuclear materials, installations and equipment 
created on their basis for producing nuclear weapons and other 
nuclear explosives or for attaining any military objectives. 
  Specialists and their families will be granted the right of 
free travel to Armenia. Tax and duty exemption will be granted 
for required goods brought into Armenia for the purpose of 
restarting the moth-balled nuclear power plant. 
  Armenian Prime-Minister Grant Bagratyan believes that the 
accord signed between the two countries marks a great step 
towards meeting Armenia's energy needs, which have been 
accumulating since the power station was moth-balled in the wake 
of the 1988 disastrous earthquake. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-16898 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov055_p_94003" </HT>


