<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Continued Support for Ter-Petrosyan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903105194 Yerevan SNARK in English 1256 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1903105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, March 18 (SNARK) -- 15.7 per cent of 
Yerevan residents would vote once again in favor of the 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan if the election were held in the 
nearest future. These are the results of the poll carried out 
in the first week of March by the "National Self-determination" 
Union (NSU)'s Public Opinion Studies Center. In 1991, when the 
President election was held, over 80 per cent of Armenian 
citizens voted for Levon Ter-Petrosyan. 
  More than a quarter of the respondents, the total number of 
which is 600, claimed they wouldn't vote for any candidate. 
13.2 per cent prefer the NSU leader Paruyr Hayrikyan. Other 
candidates' rating is far lower. 
  According to the poll, published in Yerevan newspaper 
"Ankakhutyun" (Independence), about 9 per cent of Yerevan 
residents will vote for the ruling party - Armenian National 
(Pannational] Movement. Most chances have Armenian 
Revolutionary Federation "Dashnaktsutyun" (20.8 per cent), and 
NSU (11.5 per cent). A little more than 8 per cent of the 
respondents choose to vote for the Communist Party. 

</TEXT>

