<H3> <TI>   Protest for 6th Time at Russian Headquarters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2103205194 Tallinn BNS in English 1634 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2103205194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 21, BNS -- Picketing took place for 
the sixth Monday [21 March] in a row today in front of Russian 
naval garrison headquarters in Tallinn in protest against 
continuing presence of Russian troops in the country. 
  The pickets that are held now are a form of struggle against 
a colonial empire, said Juri Adams, deputy leader of the 
Estonian National Independence Party faction in the parliament. 
  MP [member of parliament] K. Jaak Roosaare called on the 
Russian military to come out of the house and speak before the 
picketers. The Estonian MP's appeal met with no response, 
however. 
  The Estonian National Independence Party has said the Monday 
pickets in front of the house that is situated just on the foot 
of the Toompea Hill, some 200 meters from the residence of the 
Estonian Government and the parliament, will continue until the 
last Russian soldier has left the country. 

</TEXT>

