<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Director To Face Mismanagement Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1803143394 Tallinn ETA in English 0800 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1803143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 53/94] </F>
  [Text] The economic police is to bring charges of 
mismanagement against Director General of the Estonian Radio 
Herkki Haldre in the nearest future, Commissar of the economic 
police Jaak Hindriksson said. Haldre will be charged with the 
waste of state funds. The State Inspection Office accused the 
radio management in paying excessive wages and meeting 
questionable travel expenses. 
  The situation is complicated by a legal inadequacy since 
there is no legal procedure for dismissing the head of the 
radio. The national broadcasting statute stipulates that the 
radio is subordinated to the "Presidium of the Supreme Soviet", 
a body that no longer exists, while no document determines the 
relations of the radio director and the Riigikogu. Chairman of 
the parliamentary culture commission Sulev Alajde explained that 
the commission may recommend the Riigikogu to approve a new law 
on broadcasting and to keep Haldre in office for the time being. 
  Haldre is currently abroad and the Estonian Radio is headed 
by Paul Himma. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

