<H3> <TI>   Communique on Meeting of Crimean, Tatar Delegations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103221894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1922 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Lev Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol, 21 Mar -- President Yuriy Meshkov's 
administration has issued a communique on the results of the 
meeting between the delegations of Tatarstan and the Crimea, 
which was held in Kazan on 18-19 March. At the meeting, 
questions of the fulfillment of the agreement on the principles 
of trade and economic cooperation between the republics were 
discussed, and their mutual interest in the further development 
of economic, scientific-technical, cultural, and humanitarian 
ties was expressed. 
  The presidents of Tatarstan and the Crimea agreed to hold 
consultations on questions of bilateral relations and to promote 
the development of contacts between state establishments and 
public, national, and other organizations of the republics. An 
agreement was reached on the opening of trade-and-economic and 
cultural centers in Kazan and Simferopol. 

</TEXT>

