<H3> <TI>   World Bank Approves Loans for Agriculture, Engineering </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103121894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1148 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk 21 March, TASS -- Belarus will receive loans 
worth $150 to $160 million thanks to a memorandum, signed by 
chairman of the Belarus Government Vyacheslav Kebich and head of 
the World Bank mission Wafik Grace. The loans will be granted 
for a period of 15 years with the postponement of the first 
payment. 
  The loans to be received as a result of the signing of the 
memorandum will be spent on the implementation of projects in 
the spheres of forestry, agriculture, power engineering, 
transport and communal economy. Private enterprise and the 
utilisation of harmful industrial waste will be further promoted. 
  The World Bank has already granted two loans to Belarus -- 
some 17 million dollars for reforming management authorities and 
$120 million for the import of vitally necessary goods and 
materials. 

</TEXT>

