<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Belarus Envoy Discuss Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103210394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2000 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lithuanian prime minister Adolfas Slezevicius and 
Belarusian Ambassador to Lithuania Yevgeniy Voytovich have met 
to discuss relations between the two countries. Mr. Voytovich 
described the political situation in Belarus on the eve of 
presidential and parliamentary elections. Mr. Voytovich also 
asked for the prime minister's assistance in starting a 
Belarusian school in Vilnius. 
  Earlier some Lithuanian politicians voiced their discontent 
over the appointment of Mr. Voytovich to the post of the 
ambassador to Lithuania, since he had allegedly made territorial 
claims to the Lithuanian capital Vilnius. Official sources in 
Minsk have denied these allegations. 

