<H3> <TI>   Rutskoy on `Farce' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203155794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2203155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksandr Rutskoy has described as a farce and 
deception the rumors about preparations for a coup d'etat in 
connection with the appearance in the press of an anonymous 
document with a possible scenario of such an action. According 
to him, the situation is being especially dramatized in order to 
divert people's attention. He stated this during a visit to an 
agricultural fair on the territory of the All-Russian Exhibition 
Center, our correspondent Marina Chernukha reports. At the same 
time Aleksandr Rutskoy remarked that anything could be expected 
in the present situation, but he declared that, God forbid, he 
should again go through events like those of October 1993. 
Aleksandr Rutskoy is convinced that the situation in the 
country can be put right; what this needs is to ensure the 
control of the state, to determine the priorities of the 
development of the economy, to create stimuli for their 
realization, and to observe the laws. 

</TEXT>

