<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy To Sue Sobchak, Gaydar, Others </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103201794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1719 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Liberal Democratic Party leader Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy intends to sue St. Petersburg Mayor Anatoliy 
Sobchak, leader of the State Duma faction Russia's Choice Yegor 
Gaydar, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev and retired KGB 
Major-General Oleg Kalugin for defamation, Zhirinovskiy's lawyer 
Sergey Belyak told Interfax Monday. 
  He said the move was caused by statements of these political 
figures addressed at Zhirinovskiy in which he "was called an 
agent of special services and a product of the KGB, compared to 
Hitler and accused of spreading fascist ideology." Besides, 
Belyak said that Zhirinovskiy would also sue the mass media 
which reported these statements. 
  The amount of reimbursement is still being kept secret. 
Belyak said that the documents had already been prepared and 
would be presented to court within the next few days. 

</TEXT>

