<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Issues Edict on Social, Labor Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103195594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Boris Yeltsin has signed an edict on some issues 
relating to the activity of the Russian tripartite commission 
for the settlement of social and labor relations. The document 
has been adopted for the purpose of providing, within the 
framework of that commission, for regular agreement with the 
position of the president, for uniting the employers, and 
bringing together the trades unions in the sphere of 
socio-economic policy. Yuriy Yarov has been appointed the 
coordinator of the commission. 
  Boris Yeltsin also issued an edict on measures for providing 
for reforms in local government. It is established that bodies 
of state power of the subjects of the Russian Federation can set 
the date of elections to the representative bodies of local 
government in autumn this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

