<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Decrees Local Self-Government Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103183594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1546 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 21 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin issued a decree allowing regional authorities to 
announce elections to local self-government bodies for Autumn, 
the press service of the Russian leader said on Monday. 
  "The decree says that bodies of state power of the subjects 
of the Russian Federation taking into account local conditions 
can announce elections to legislative bodies of local 
self-government for Autumn 1994", the press service said. 

</TEXT>

