<H3> <TI>   Grachev Hopes for Defense Budget Increase </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2203131594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 22 Mar 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM2203131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Grachev Expects Money"] </F>
  [Text] The Russian Federation defense minister has voiced 
the hope that the ministry's budget for 1994 will nonetheless be 
increased. The defense minister noted that the proposed total 
defense budget (37 trillion rubles) is being insisted on solely 
by the Finance Ministry. In his opinion, it would meet only 
46-47 percent of the Armed Forces' requirements. 

</TEXT>

