<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Power Supply to Air Defense Command Threatened </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2103151794 Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA in Russian 19 Mar 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2103151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Women Block Flights"] </F>
  [Text] Something extraordinary has occurred in the Air 
Defense Troops' air regiment on the island of Sakhalin. Wives 
of officers and ensigns went onto the runway and started 
blocking flights. The cause of this was a chronic lack of money 
-- the 1egiment's servicemen have not been paid since January. 
  Colonel Semen Romanenko, deputy chief of the Air Defense 
Troops Financial and Economic Directorate, told an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent that money has today been transferred to the Far 
Eastern servicemen for a specific purpose. In his opinion, 
however, the question of money to pay servicemen and to finance 
the Air Defense Troops has not been resolved as a whole. 
Special concern is aroused by the debt of 18 billion rubles [R] 
in respect of Moscow Regional Power Administration accounts. 
This organization is warning of the possible disconnection of 
the Central Command Post and other important installations which 
ensure Russia's national security. 
  Col. Romanenko blames the disastrous situation with regard 
to 
funding the Air Defense Troops' Far Eastern units on a shortfall 
of R2 billion compared with the planned provision. The 
ITAR-TASS correspondent managed to ascertain from the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Defense that not only the families of 
Sakhalin servicemen are suffering from a lack of money. In 
February one-fourth of Russia's servicemen did not receive their 
pay, and there will be still more in March. 

</TEXT>

