<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Chernomyrdin meet Krasnodar Kray Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203114494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2203114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin and Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin have held a meeting in Sochi with 
Nikolay Yegorov, the head of administration of Krasnodar Kray, 
and Sochi Mayor Nikolay Karpov. It was decided to set up a 
working group to draw up a treaty between the federal agencies 
of state power and the bodies running the kray concerning 
demarcation of functions in line with the Constitution of the 
Russian Federation and the Federation Treaty, taking account of 
the particular features of Krasnodar Kray. The Russian 
Federation's Security Council has been instructed to prepare a 
package of questions on Krasnodar Kray for consideration at one 
of its upcoming sessions. 

