<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Steppe Code' To Replace Kalmyk Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2203102794 Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN in Russian 22 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2203102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from roundup of ITAR-TASS reports: "Steppe Code </F>
Instead of Constitution?"] 
  [Text] The Kalmykia parliament has decided to replace the 
constitution with a new fundamental law for the republic. At 
its extraordinary session it examined normative documents for 
the adoption of the so-called Steppe Code instead of the 
constitution in operation at present. The mechanism for 
reworking the republic's legislative basis was approved by 25 
parliamentarians who have thus decided the fate of the entire 
people living on the territory of Kalmykia. 
  Less than two weeks have been assigned for a discussion of 
the Steppe Code. After it has been adopted, if it is adopted, 
the republic's supreme legislative organ will be the people's 
khural, which Kalmyk President Kirsan Ilyumzhinov could dissolve 
at any moment, considering that it is failing to ensure 
stability in society. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

