<H3> <TI>   Swedish-Latvians Protest Withdrawal Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2103212394 Tallinn BNS in English 1924 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2103212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 21, BNS -- Swedish-Latvians' 
organizations issued a statement Monday [21 March] protesting 
the initialed agreement between Latvia and Russia on the Skrunda 
radar station and the status of retired Russian servicemen in 
the Baltic country. 
  The Latvian Government in fact legalized the Russian 
occupation by initialing the agreement, according to the 
statement. 
  The organizations urge the Saeima (parliament) to decline 
the 
agreement's ratification because the document is evidently 
hostile to the intersts of the Latvian nation. It may also 
provoke unpredictable consequences in the future. 
  The group also calls on President Guntis Ulmanis not to sign 
the document. 
  The statement is signed by the Latvian National Independence 
Movement's Swedish department, the Latvian National Fund, the 
Swedish-Latvians Central Council and the Swedish Daugavas Vanagi 
organization. 

</TEXT>

