<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Crimean Pre-Election Situation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Electoral Committee Resolves To Support Poll </H4>
<F P=102> WS2203103294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2203103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The decree on polling citizens issued by the 
Crimean president on 10 March prompted yesterday's fourth 
session of the Central Electoral Committee of the Crimea. In 
the course of the preceding sessions held jointly with 
presidential representatives, the committee drafted a compromise 
version of the decree on holding the poll. The Central 
Electoral Committee resolved to consider it possible to grant 
organizational support to President Meshkov in holding the poll 
in such a way as not to contradict laws or endanger the 
elections. 

</TEXT>

