<H4>   Crimea Officers Meet </H4>
<F P=102> MK2203143094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 22 Mar 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2203143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Crimea"] 
  [Text] An election meeting of the Officers Union of Crimea 
comprising 500 servicemen of a pro-Russia orientation was held 
in Sevastopol on 20 March. The Officers Union of Crimea 
nominated 11 candidates for the Supreme Soviet of Crimea who 
include Black Sea Fleet servicemen. The Officers Union turned 
to Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin and the Russian 
Federation State Duma with a request to speed up the solution of 
the question on placing Sevastopol and the Black Sea Fleet under 
Russian jurisdiction. An appeal to Republic of Crimea President 
Yuriy Meshkov contains a call to create on the basis of the 
Officers Union a National Guard of Crimea and, in this 
connection, to eliminate on the peninsula's territory the 
National Guard of Ukraine. 

