<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Forecasts Rising Unemployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2203141094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 22 Mar 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> MK2203141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Unemployment Growing in Ukraine"] </F>
  [Text] As of the end of 1993, around 93,000 people were 
registered in Ukraine as unemployed. According to the Ukrainian 
Labor Ministry's forecast, the figure is expected to rise to 1 
million by the end of 1994. Meanwhile, Ukrainian Deputy Prime 
Minister Valentin Landik has said that the number of people out 
of work will rise even higher following mass bankruptcies of 
enterprises. By year's end, up to 3.4 million of Ukraine's 
able-bodied citizens, that is, every ninth resident of the 
republic, will be fully or partially unemployed. 

</TEXT>

