<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Rejects Assessment of Nuclear Plant Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203120194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1500 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2203120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kiev -- UNIAN has learned that Ukraine's State 
Committee for Control of Work Safety in Nuclear Engineering 
[Derzhatomnahlyad] disagreed with the safety level assessment of 
the fire at the Khmelnitskiy AES given by the State Committee 
for the Use of Nuclear Power [Derzhkomatom]. The head of 
Derzhatomnahlyad's scientific and technical directorate, Vadym 
Hryshchenko, told UNIAN that although the radioactive situation 
had not deteriorated, a fire always posed a potential threat of 
weakening safety control systems in the power unit. Therefore, 
this case should be classified on the international scale of 
incidents as first level, not zero level. Derzhatomnahlyad has 
reported its verdict to the International Atomic Energy Agency. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

