<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fleet Fails To Inform Ministry of Military Exercise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203112194 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 19 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2203112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Antisubmarine Exercise in the Black </F>
Sea Fleet"] 
  [Text] On the evening on 17 March, near the Crimean 
shores, a large-scale Black Sea Fleet exercise started. It was 
meant to develop methods of conducting combat operations against 
submarines of an imaginary adversary with an active air force 
counteraction. On the morning of 18 March, as many as 25 ships, 
two submarines, and five auxiliary ships were already involved 
in the exercise. They occupied the area from Donuzlav (western 
shore) to Kerch (in the east). The exercise had been 
coordinated with Russia's Ministry of Defense. As our 
correspondent was told at the Press Center of Ukraine's Ministry 
of Defense, the Black Sea Fleet Command had not informed 
Ukraine's Ministry of Defense of this exercise. 

</TEXT>

