<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Power Ministry To Cut Heating Supplies Early </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203164094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1420 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2203164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- A UNIAN correspondent 
learned today that heating in Ukraine's residential buildings 
and at enterprises will be switched off before the end of March 
rather than on 15 April as was the case previously. Commenting 
on the situation, Oleksiy Sheberstov, Ukraine's first deputy 
minister of power engineering and electrification, said 
Ukraine's fuel supplies are rapidly diminishing. At the same 
time, consumers owe 8,000 billion karbovantsi to the ministry, 
which is the reason why it lacks the money to buy oil and gas 
for heating. 

</TEXT>

