<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Munition Depot, Russian Border Posts Shelled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103144194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1143 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munition depots of the Tajikistan Defense Ministry 
in the settlement of Aini, 6 km outside Dushanbe, came under 
fire last night and in early hours of Monday. A source close to 
military circles told INTERFAX that the depots stored weapons, 
fuels and lubricants as well as munition. There were no 
casualties or damage. Appropriate agencies started an 
investigation. 
  The area of the 12th and 13th posts of the Moskovskiy border 
guard unit were fired at with heavy machine guns and rocket 
shells from inside Afghanistan at 16:30 on March 20. The border 
guards returned fire and wiped out the enemy firing positions. 
There were no casualties among the Russian border guards. Armed 
groups and hardware of Tajik opposition were seen to move 
actively in the Afghan area opposite the 1st post of the Pyanj 
border guard unit. 

</TEXT>

