<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Draft Resolution To Clarify Amnesty Bill Application </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103163494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1551 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2103163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 21 TASS -- Not a single provision in 
the State Duma resolution on amnesty will be reversed or 
reconsidered, Duma Deputy Chairman Valentin Kovalyov said. 
  Kovalyov said that a working group has prepared a draft 
resolution on the application of the amnesty resolution. He did 
not rule out the possibility that the draft may be submitted to 
the Duma on Friday. 
  "The idea of the document is to specify the provisions which 
may be interpreted in different ways. Particularly, the draft 
stipulates that the amnesty resolution shall not stop legal 
proceedings instituted against those who committed criminal 
offences during the August 1991, May 1993 and October 1993 
events which were not directly connected with these events," 
Kovalyov said. 
  In accordance with this provision, marauders who plundered 
the parliament building during the October revolt in Moscow or 
thieves will not be amnestied. "Only those are subject to 
amnesty whose actions were in the cause-effect relation with the 
political events in August, May and October," Kovalyov explained. 
  He noted that the draft resolution is the result of 
agreement 
between all participants in the work on it, including deputies, 
representatives of the public prosecutor's office, the 
ministries of justice and foreign affairs and presidential 
representatives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

