<H4>   Iran Denies Mission Theory </H4>
<F P=102> LD2203094694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0929 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2203094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Kuzmin] </F>
  [Text] Tehran March 22 TASS -- The Iranian Foreign Ministry 
rejected on Tuesday reports that the Iranian cargo plane C-130 
which crashed last Friday in Nagorno-Karabakh, was on a 
reconnaissance mission. 
  A ministry official told ITAR-TASS that an official 
statement 
of the Foreign Ministry on the matter will follow soon. 
  The catastrophe killing 34 people occured when a 
Tehran-bound 
Iranian cargo plane instead of entering the Armenian airspace 
suddenly changed course due to unknown reasons and hit the 
ground several miles off Stepanakert, the administrative centre 
of the disputed Armenian enclave in Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

