  [Text] Moscow, March 21 (AFP) -- Japanese Foreign Minister 
Tsutomu Hata demanded Monday that North Korea let international 
experts carry out a full inspection of its nuclear facilities 
and criticized Pyonyang's renewed threat to pull out of the 
Nuclear non- Proliferation Treaty (NPT). 
  "Japan is worried by the fact that we could not obtain 
confirmation of the non-use by North Korea of nuclear materials 
for military purposes," Hata said at a news conference. 

