<H3> <TI>   Delegation Leader Comments on CSCE Economic Forum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803211294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2007 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Yakovlev] </F>
  [Text] Prague March 18 TASS -- The economic forum of the 
Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe (CSCE) 
considers European economic problems, paying special attention 
to the difficulties which are faced by the countries 
implementing economic reforms in the transitional period, Pavel 
Smirnov, head of the Department of Economic Cooperation of the 
Russian Foreign Ministry, told ITAR-TASS on Friday, after the 
second session of the economic forum concluded here. 
  According to Smirnov, who led the Russian delegation, 
participants in the session focussed mainly on economic 
situation in the countries undergoing economic reforms. 
  The Russian delegates drew attention to regional integrating 
processes with a view to preventing discrimination against the 
Russian Federation. They also raised the question of developing 
production cooperation within the framework of the "Partnership 
for Peace" initiative. 
  We should immediately begin working on the economic aspects 
of the initiative, first of all, in the interests of our 
industry and state military-industrial complex, Smirnov said. 
  The third session of the CSCE economic forum will be held in 
June 1995. 

</TEXT>

